videos.headline: Barkley starts game off with 69-yard TD
videos.description: Saquon Barkley takes the direct snap 69 yards for the touchdown on the second play from scrimmage for Penn State.

videos.headline: O'Korn sacked on third down
videos.description: Curtis Cothran gets to the Michigan Quarterback on third down for a loss of five yards.

videos.headline: McSorley gets 22 yards on the ground
videos.description: Trace McSorley takes it himself up the middle for  a 22-yard gain.

videos.headline: Barkley takes the pitch for a 2nd TD
videos.description: Saquon Barkley runs in a 15-yard touchdown on the pitch from Trace McSorley.

videos.headline: McSorley picked off in red zone
videos.description: Trace McSorley is intercepted by David Long who returns it 25 yards before he's tackled by the Penn State quarterback.

videos.headline: Higdon scores on fourth down for Michigan
videos.description: Karan Higdon runs in a one-yard touchdown for the Wolverines on fourth-and-one. Quinn Nordin would miss the extra-point attempt.

videos.headline: Hamilton goes up for a 27-yard catch
videos.description: Trace McSorley connects with DaeSean Hamilton with a great leaping catch over his defender for a 27-yard gain.

videos.headline: PSU VS MICH
McSorley scores easily for Penn State
videos.description: Trace McSorley uses the play-action to perfection to score a three-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: PSU's offense rules en route to 21-13 halftime lead
videos.description: The 303 total yards by Penn State in the first half are the most allowed in any half by a Jim Harbaugh Michigan team.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (PSU's offense rules en route to 21-13 halftime lead) 2017/10/21

videos.headline: Isaac drives through for a Michigan TD
videos.description: Ty Isaac picks up a few big blocks and dives in for the six-yard rushing touchdown.

videos.headline: Franklin: 'Gotta be more consistent on defense'
videos.description: Penn State head coach James Franklin saw adjustments made by Michigan in the first half and wants his team to react better in the second half.

videos.headline: Hamilton turns slant into 26 yards
videos.description: DaeSean Hamilton earns a quick 26 yards for Penn State on a short pass over the middle from Trace McSorley.

videos.headline: McSorley weaves and dives for 2nd TD
videos.description: Trace McSorley finds his way outside and dives for the pylon on a 13-yard touchdown for the Nittany Lions.

videos.headline: O'Korn fumbles for Michigan
videos.description: John O'Korn is hit from behind by Christian Campbell and fumbles the ball before Robert Windsor recovers.

videos.headline: Barkley bobbles and scores big TD
videos.description: Saquon Barkley juggles a 42-yard pass from Trace McSorley but holds on for the score padding Penn State's lead.

videos.headline: McSorley extends for his 3rd TD
videos.description: Trace McSorley winds through the defense and stretches out for the nine-yard rushing touchdown.

videos.headline: McSorley scrambles into red zone
videos.description: Trace McSorley is on the move again with a 19-yard run to set up Penn State in the red zone.

videos.headline: Franklin: 'Happy to be 1-0 this week'
videos.description: Penn State head coach James Franklin says his team will enjoy this win for an hour before moving on to Ohio State next week.

videos.headline: McSorley: 'Last year motivated us'
videos.description: Trace McSorley and Saquon Barkley share their thoughts on Penn State's dominating win over Michigan.

videos.headline: Michigan defense flattened by Penn State
videos.description: Chris Fowler and Kirk Herbstreit discuss Penn State's convincing win over Michigan and the Nittany Lion's next challenge, Ohio State.

videos.headline: Penn State pours it on late against Michigan
videos.description: Saquon Barkley rushes for 108 yards and two scores while catching another as No. 2 Penn State scores the final 28 points of the game en route to a 42-13 victory against No. 19 Michigan.

videos.headline: Barkley, Penn State roll past Michigan
videos.description: Heisman hopeful Saquon Barkley's three total touchdowns and Nittany Lions QB Trace McSorley's four total scores help Penn State dominate Michigan 42-13 on Saturday night.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Barkley, Penn State roll past Michigan) 2017/10/21 ESHEET SCEU

videos.headline: Barkley helps Heisman case in White Out rout
videos.description: It's another stellar day at the office for the Nittany Lions junior, who thrills a record crowd with three more touchdowns.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Barkley helps Heisman case in White Out rout) 2017/10/21 ESHEET ENHL
